<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-115-176  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 115 176.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>High Technology Business  April 1989 v9 n4 p10(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Do-it-yourself gas pumps. ('smart' pumps)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilson, James.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>New gas pumps that are a cross between an automated teller machineand a business computer offer substantial time-saving in recordkeeping as well as the potential for 24-hour, unattended service.andO;One user estimates the savings at about 20 minutes at the end ofeach shift.andP;  The Wayne Div of Dresser Industries, supplier of theelectronics systems for the pumps, says the electronics add about10 percent to the price of a pump.andP;  The concept of unattendedpumps is being favorably received in Europe; they handle one-fifthof volume on Sweden.andP;  Insurance difficulties are a stumbling blockin the US.andP;  Robotic refueling, which would permit motorists toremain behind the wheel, is a possibility if the automobileindustry will agree on a standard location for the gas cap.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dresser Industries Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    DI.andO;Topic:     AutomationAutomobile Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>